curl -XPOST 'http://localhost:9200/electronic_products/_create/14236' -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"product_name": "SGM66025", "table_name": "GENERAL DESCRIPTION", "content": "GENERAL DESCRIPTION  The SGM66025 is a synchronous Boost converter with  integrated load disconnect function. The device is  capable to start up from 0.8V (TYP) input, and the input  voltage can operate down to 0.6V after start-up. Output  voltage ranges from 1.8V to 4V. The device integrates a  1.8A power switch with a fixed 1MHz switching  frequency. Bypass mode is also supported when VIN is  higher than VOUT.  The P channel synchronous rectifier provides short-  circuit protection and load disconnect feature to  minimize leakage current drawn from the input source.  The device also implements soft-start feature to  minimize inrush current during start-up.  The SGM66025 implements various protection features  such as short-circuit protection and thermal shutdown  to improve device robustness.  The SGM66025 is available in a Green TSOT-23-8  package and operates over an ambient temperature  range of -40℃ to +85℃.  "}'
